-- Otto Aims to Become Market Leader in Brazil, Abendblatt Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-05-10T08:07:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/otto-aims-to-become-market-leader-in-brazil-abendblatt-reports.html
Otto Group sees “significant
potential” to grow in  Brazil  and aims to become the market
leader in the country’s online fashion trade within five years
by raising sales to $500 million,  Hamburger Abendblatt  reported
today, citing Chief Executive Officer Hans-Otto Schrader.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
